    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it feels like the \"multiplier effect\" is a bit of a reach when we're talking about a mom-and-pop shop. if i have to fire a part-time person just to pay the others more, the local economy isn't really winning, is it? do you think there's a point where these policies just stop being about helping workers and start being more about political optics?",
